Fix luiginim's freetype handling for prawk's dynamic-freetype + small-binary
constraint.

Upstream luiginim (last updated 3 years prior to 2026-04) has issues that
block the project's constraint of dynamic-linked freetype on Linux with a
hyper-small binary:

  1. The -I path for the vendored freetype headers is unquoted AND uses
     `file.nim/..` which some path resolvers (cc1 on modern glibc) reject
     with "Not a directory". Switching to currentSourcePath().parentDir()
     with embedded quotes fixes both (unquoted path also breaks on paths
     containing spaces, e.g. "/.../SSS-Core/Nim Projects/...").

  2. A hard {.error.} requires -d:freetypeStatic, which would compile the
     400KB vendored freetype into our binary. Static freetype was
     explicitly dropped back in pass 0.

  3. The non-static fallback adds `-lfreetype`, which requires a
     libfreetype.so symlink that's often absent on release distros (we have
     libfreetype.so.6 only). Prawk passes `-l:libfreetype.so.6` from
     config.nims instead, so luiginim's passL is dropped.

Applied by scripts/prep-vendor.sh into build/luiginim/ so vendor/luiginim/
stays byte-identical to upstream.

--- a/src/luigi.nim
+++ b/src/luigi.nim
@@ -1,3 +1,5 @@
+import std/os
+
 when defined(lFreetype):
   import freetype
 
@@ -26,16 +28,12 @@
 
 when defined(lFreetype):
   {.passC: "-DUI_FREETYPE".}
-  {.passC: "-I" & currentSourcePath() & "/../luigi/source/freetype".}
+  {.passC: "-I\"" & currentSourcePath().parentDir() & "/luigi/source/freetype\"".}
   
   when not defined(freetypeStatic):
-    {.error: "Please use -d:freetypeStatic when compiling".}
-
     # if you still dont want to define it... (for some reason)
-    when not defined(vcc):
-      {.passL: "-lfreetype".} 
-    else:
-      {.link: "freetype.lib".}
+    # prawk passes its own -l:libfreetype.so.6 from config.nims, so no passL here.
+    discard
 
 when defined(lDebug):
   {.passC: "-DUI_DEBUG".}
